<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
How To Make Charm Work in RvR:<P>Charming a player works just like charming a mob.  There is thing a charmed player can do that a mob can't.  He can /release.  When he does this, he counts as if you had killed him and he had typed release.  However, you do NOT lose him as a pet exactly.  You retain an exact copy of him except it is now a mob.  When it dies it just disappears.  He may even travel from his bindspot out to the frontier and you could sic your pet, a copy of him, on him.  Laugh while you kill a people with themselves.<P>He could also opt not to release.  He can wait as long as he wants.  He gets to chat while charmed (at least /g and /send) and if you die he is no longer charmed.  That means if he expects his groupmates to be killing you quickly he doesn't want to /release.  No reason to /release if you are effectively going to be rezzed in a second.<P>How's that for fixing the problem with getting pets on the frontier?  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>-Zanthis
</FONT>
