Silly?  As Battik points it Charming PCs is no more silly than chain stunning them, and Mythic permits that.  If you give them the choice to release, it does NOT control them for any time at all.  It is a less unbalanced idea than having archers that can one and two shot me and to whom I may do nothing in return.  Silly? Perhaps only in that Mythic saw the need to coddle other classes at the expense of the sorcerer.  Will it be implemented? I agree unlikely, because Mythic is obviously going to be too gunshy to do it.  If that's what you meant by silly, then I concur.  If however, by silly you meant ridiculously unbalancing, I'd really like to know why, because I honestly don't see it...I think MANY things already in this game are WAY more unbalancing than that, and most of them work AGAINST sorcs.  AND even if it WERE unbalanced in favor of sorcs, it would only partially make up for some of the unbalancing elements that already exist against them.  What did I miss?  I fail to see the "silly" in the suggestion...it's a "fantasy" game as it is?  Isn't playing one a little silly too?<P><BR>Oh, and i3ullseye, I like your idea too  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><BR>Taco
