Given that I was once again one-shot killed for over 730 points by an archer tonight wearing ebony cloth, with my armor spell up, I simply cannot feel sympathy.  I ended up logging for the night...couldn't face the 20 minutes it would take to get back to the fight again.  That, my friend, was a one-shot death.  If they would be so horrible resulting from a charm with almost no range, and which DOES get resisted, then I think the nerf bat simply HAS to do away with archers who have exactly the same ability.  As to whether the person is forced to do something he doesn't want to do, well, he should be able to just suicide release...it's what happens to me all the time.  I would have relished the possiblity that I could have been used against my friends if it gave me a chance.  I'd just monitor what I was doing and if it got too nasty I'd choose the suicide option.  For me, being charmed, with suicide option, would be BETTER than one shot by archer...it gives me some choice and some possibility of rescue by my friends, who would, no doubt, know to target the charmer.  <P>This is a game ppl, you wouldn't REALLY be hurting your friends  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> <P>I'd just like the rules to be a little more even for the classes...shall we say we take 3 spell lines at random from each caster class and make them uselss or interrupts only in RVR until this is hashed out...that would be fair, right?  And 6 abilities from tanks and those classes that get double our spec points.  I'd be happy with that  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">
