<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Charming is too exploitable in RvR.  Among other things, you could make charmed players attack mobs and that would force exp loss.  It would be a coding nightmare to try to fix all the exploits.  Charm is much worse than just death and it is from just one cast.  Charm would be far too powerful.<P>Forcing release or giving them the release option would be a solution, but that is far too powerful also.  In RvR, death is usually not that bad, because they just get rezzed again.  Forcing a release takes them out of the game for 20-40 minutes while they get back to the group which is just too powerful.  No spell should result in  release, that renders rez useless and would make sorcerers stratigically overpowering.<P>Charm as it stands in this game should not be implemented against players, because it is far too powerful, a fate worse than death with just one cast which is rarely resisted.
