<B>Originally posted by mad sorcerer:</B><BR>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>Charming is too exploitable in RvR.  Among other things, you could make charmed players attack mobs and that would force exp loss.  It would be a coding nightmare to try to fix all the exploits.  Charm is much worse than just death and it is from just one cast.  Charm would be far too powerful.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>Actually, it wouldn't be that hard to prevent Sorcerers from forcing an xp death on players.  Here is an easy solution: Charmed players cannot suffer an xp death while charmed, period.  Once you are no longer charmed (either because the Sorcerer let you go or because the Sorcerer died) you cannot have an xp death for 5-10 minutes or until you zone.  [edit: added this-&gt;] If you die during this period, once you are rezzed (or /release) you are subject to the normal rules for xp deaths.<P>Can anyone think of a way to force an xp death on a player given that rule?<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>Forcing release or giving them the release option would be a solution, but that is far too powerful also.  In RvR, death is usually not that bad, because they just get rezzed again.  Forcing a release takes them out of the game for 20-40 minutes while they get back to the group which is just too powerful.  No spell should result in  release, that renders rez useless and would make sorcerers stratigically overpowering.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>"Death usually isn't that bad"...unless a whole army camps your corpse and you have to /release.  Same deal here.  There would be times you'd want to /release because rescue wasn't coming anytime soon and their would be times you'd just sit it out.  Keep in mind in my proposal you still had chatting ability, so the Sorcerer would have to understand you would be relaying strategic information to his enemy.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>Charm as it stands in this game should not be implemented against players, because it is far too powerful, a fate worse than death with just one cast which is rarely resisted.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>Rarely resisted huh?  Well <I>I</I> haven't been able to cast charm on players yet so I have no idea what the resist rate is in RvR.  How is it you know how tough charm is to resist in RvR?<P>-Zanthis
