would HAVE to lose your chat ability or it woudl be a horrible joke, and open to even MORE exploitation.<P>How?<P>So you can't speak or understand the enemies language. but what if you had a buddy in the enemy realm, and he purposely charms you? thats right, now he can run around enemy posistions safe and sound, reporting all he sees back to his realm free of ANY repurcussions.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>Rarely resisted huh?  Well <I>I</I> haven't been able to cast charm on players yet so I have no idea what the resist rate is in RvR.  How is it you know how tough charm is to resist in RvR?<P>-Zanthis<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>In RvR? no clue. But it is one of the least resisted spells i cast from day to day usage. Further, i am not so sure it is EVER truly resisted, but simply fails. maybe it bypasses resist code, and PCs are not coded to handle spells of this nature properly anyway.<P>See, regardless of what some may think, we analysed and hashed out a LOT of this in BETA. many items now reside in what is called the dead horse stables, where dead horse topics go to draw flies. when a Dev, or a TL, or any of the older BETA testers seems to dismiss something offhand, don't assume they are being flippiant. there is quite a bit of factual and experienced information supporting these decisions.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
